Class PrefsHighScores

  • java.lang.Object
    • dynamicStorage.PrefsHighScores
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrefsHighScores
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class holds all of the player's preferred settings and the high scores for the particular program that the player is using.
    Author:
    Stanton Parham (stparham@ncsu.edu)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      PrefsHighScores()
      Creates a new PrefsHighScores object; THIS SHOULD ONLY BE USED IF THERE IS NOT ALREADY ONE OF THESE OBJECTS PRESENT! AFTER CREATING THIS OBJECT IT WILL BE SERIALIZED INTO A FILE AND RELOADED EACH TIME THE PROGRAM RUNS SO IT WILL NEVER NEED TO BE CONSTRUCTED AGAIN.

        public boolean addHighScore(java.lang.String playerName,
                            int score)
        Attempts to add a passed in score to the high scores if the score is greater than one of the current high scores;
        Parameters:
        playerName - the player's name that achieved the passed in score;
        score - the score to be set
        Returns:
        whether or not the score passed in was set as a new high score;
